nodes.text: Star Wars: Rebel Warrior was a canceled video game that was planned by LucasArts. The game was to focus on a Wookiee warrior trying to drive the Galactic Empire out of their home.
According to some sources, the game's plot was to focus on an unnamed enslaved Wookiee warrior from Kashyyyk that would have been trying to drive the Galactic Empire out of their home.

At a one unspecified point, LucasArts tried to develop Star Wars: Rebel Warrior as part of its planned Star Wars: Rebel video game series, which also included other titles like Star Wars: Rebel Agent, Star Wars: Rebel Fury, Star Wars: Rebel Scum and Star Wars: Rebel Jedi.
